query:
I want a Conductor workflow that summarizes a blog post with Claude. Anthropic's API is already reachable from this server — I've previously called https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages from an HTTP task and it worked. The new workflow should accept `{"text": "..."}` as input and return a one-sentence summary. After you write it, also review this existing workflow that I want to migrate — it currently uses an HTTP task to OpenAI:

```json
{
  "name": "classify_ticket",
  "version": 1,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "name": "call_openai",
      "taskReferenceName": "call_openai",
      "type": "HTTP",
      "inputParameters": {
        "http_request": {
          "uri": "https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions",
          "method": "POST",
          "headers": {"Authorization": "Bearer ${workflow.input.openai_key}", "Content-Type": "application/json"},
          "body": {
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "messages": [
              {"role": "system", "content": "Classify support tickets as billing, technical, or other. Reply with one word."},
              {"role": "user", "content": "${workflow.input.ticket}"}
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "outputParameters": {"category": "${call_openai.output.response.body.choices[0].message.content}"},
  "schemaVersion": 2
}
```
